British Isles
Channel Islands









Guernsey







The Channel Islands have a legacy of political and economic stability with constitutions and legal systems that go back many centuries. 
Our Guernsey office* is home to a large team of dedicated professionals who provide valuable local knowledge, the advantage of a truly international team of specialists, and access to a complete range of wealth management services through our global network of offices**.



PO Box 48, Canada Court, Upland Road
                        St. Peter Port, Guernsey
                        Channel Islands, GY1 3BQ




Tel. +44-1481-744000***
Fax +44-1481-744001



Royal Bank of Canada (Channel Islands) Limited ("the Bank") is a licensed bank in Guernsey and a participant in the Guernsey Banking Deposit Compensation Scheme ("the Guernsey Scheme"). For further information on the Guernsey Scheme please refer to the States of Guernsey official website by clicking here.
Published accounts for Royal Bank of Canada (Channel Islands) Limited are available on request. 
* RBC entities in Guernsey that provide financial services (as defined by the relevant Guernsey law) are regulated by the Guernsey Financial Services Commission.
                ** Depending on your citizenship and/or residence, some products and services may not be available to you or may only be available to you from certain RBC Wealth Management offices.
                *** Calls may be recorded.

 









Jersey







The Channel Islands have a legacy of political and economic stability with constitutions and legal systems that go back many centuries.
Our Jersey office* is home to a large team of dedicated professionals who provide valuable local knowledge, the advantage of a truly international team of specialists, and access to a complete range of wealth management services through our global network of offices**.



Gaspé House
                        66-72 Esplanade
                        St. Helier, Jersey 
                        JE2 3QT




Tel. +44-1534-283000***
Fax +44-1534-283801



Royal Bank of Canada (Channel Islands) Limited, Jersey Branch ("the Bank") is a licensed bank in Jersey and a participant in the Jersey Bank Depositors Compensation Scheme ("the Jersey Scheme"). For further information on the Jersey Scheme, please refer to the States of Jersey official website by clicking here.
Published accounts for Royal Bank of Canada (Channel Islands) Limited are available on request. 
* RBC entities in Jersey that provide financial services (as defined by the relevant Jersey law) are regulated by the Jersey Financial Services Commission.
                ** Depending on your citizenship and/or residence, some products and services may not be available to you or may only be available to you from certain RBC Wealth Management offices.
                *** Calls may be recorded.

 


United Kingdom









Edinburgh







The RBC Corporate Employee & Executive Services (RBC cees) team in Edinburgh delivers high quality plan management, administration and employee trust solutions for share and stock plans, international pension plans and employee benefit plans.
The Edinburgh office also provides access to RBC Wealth Management's worldwide network of offices. 
Find out more by visiting the RBC cees website. 



Exchange Tower, 9th Floor
                        19 Canning Street
                        Edinburgh, Scotland EH3 8EG




Tel. +44-131-222-3600**
Fax +44-131-222-3601



* Depending on your citizenship and/or residence, some products and services may not be available to you or may only be available to you from certain RBC Wealth Management offices.
                ** Calls may be recorded.

 









London







RBC has had a presence in London since 1910.
Our London office is home to a large team of dedicated professionals who provide valuable local knowledge, the advantage of a truly international team of specialists, and access to a complete range of wealth management services through our global network of offices*.



Riverbank House, 2 Swan Lane
                        London, United Kingdom, EC4R 3BF 




Tel. +44-0-20-7653-4000**
Fax +44-0-20-7329-6144



Clients should always remember that the value of investments may fall as well as rise and that they may not get back the full amount that they originally invested.
Fraud Prevention
Maximise your privacy and security, by being informed, which is often the best defence against fraud.
Latest Alert
* Depending on your citizenship and/or residence, some products and services may not be available to you or may only be available to you from certain RBC Wealth Management offices.
                ** Calls may be recorded.
RBC Wealth Management is a business name used by subsidiaries of Royal Bank of Canada. Details regarding London subsidiaries are set out below: 
ROYAL BANK OF CANADA INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT (U.K.) LIMITED Registered in England and Wales No. 2494634. Registered Address: Riverbank House, 2 Swan Lane, London, EC4R 3BF. VAT No. 365 345640. Authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority for UK investment management business.
ROYAL BANK OF CANADA INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT (USA) LIMITED Registered in England and Wales No. 3327984. Registered Address: Riverbank House, 2 Swan Lane, London, EC4R 3BF. VAT No. 365 345640. Authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority for UK investment management business and is registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission as an Investment Adviser for US investment advisory business. 
RBC EUROPE LIMITED Registered in England and Wales No. 995939. Registered Address: Riverbank House, 2 Swan Lane, London, EC4R 3BF. Authorised by the Prudential Regulation Authority and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority and the Prudential Regulation Authority for UK banking business. 
ROYAL BANK OF CANADA, LONDON BRANCH Royal Bank of Canada, London Branch is a branch of Royal Bank of Canada, a Canadian chartered bank registered under Part XXIII of the Companies Act 1985 with registration number BR000548 whose London Branch is at Riverbank House, 2 Swan Lane, London, EC4R 3BF. Authorised and regulated by Office of the Superintendent of Financial Institutions of Canada. Authorised by the Prudential Regulation Authority. Subject to regulation by the Financial Conduct Authority and limited regulation by the Prudential Regulation Authority. Details about the extent of our regulation by the Prudential Regulation Authority are available from us on request. Royal Bank of Canada is a member of the RBC Group. For information about our group of companies, please visit www.rbc.com. 
Banking: Your eligible deposits with RBC Europe Limited are protected up to a total of £85,000 by the Financial Services Compensation Scheme, the UK's deposit protection scheme. Any deposits you hold above the £85,000 limit are not covered. Please visit the FSCS website www.fscs.org.uk for further information. 
Investment: You may be entitled to compensation from the scheme if we cannot meet our obligations. This depends on the type of business and the circumstances of the claim. Most types of investment business are covered for up to a total of £50,000. 
For further information about the FSCS (including the amounts covered and eligibility to claim) please refer to the FSCS website (www.fscs.org.uk).

 





